HEADWORD: Hypotrochoid
<hw>Hy`po*tro"choid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>hypo-</ets> + <ets>trochoid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Geom.)</fld> <def>A
curve, traced by a point in the radius, or radius produced, of a circle
which rolls upon the concave side of a fixed circle. See
<er>Hypocycloid</er>, <er>Epicycloid</er>, and
<er>Trochoid</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hypotyposis</ent>⟦br⟧
